Text:
There are several ways to achieve what you want. Here are two examples:

**Using `display: inline-block;`**

<!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false -->

<!-- language: lang-css -->

    .player {
      margin: 10px;
      border: 1px solid red;
      padding: 10px;
      text-align: center;
      display: inline-block;
    }

<!-- language: lang-html -->

    <div class="players">
        <div class="player">
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/100">
            <p>Username - Level</p>
        </div>

        <div class="player">
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/100">
            <p>Username - Level</p>
        </div>
    </div>

<!-- end snippet -->

**Using `display: flex;`**

<!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false -->

<!-- language: lang-css -->

    .players {
      display: flex;
    }

    .player {
      margin: 10px;
      border: 1px solid red;
      padding: 10px;
      text-align: center;
    }

<!-- language: lang-html -->

    <div class="players">
        <div class="player">
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/100">
            <p>Username - Level</p>
        </div>

        <div class="player">
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/100">
            <p>Username - Level</p>
        </div>
    </div>

<!-- end snippet -->

Both solutions need you to wrap your elements inside a wrapping `div`.
